# AKOS Finance Ops (FINOPS)

Use this rule whenever authoring or reviewing artefacts that touch
**FINOPS canonical CSVs** (Compliance `finops/`), **Finance-area doctrine**
(rev-rec, pricing, tax calendars), **counterparty MDM**, **`finops.registered_fact`**
entity gate, or **FINOPS mirror / recon** evidence. Codifies the mechanical
layer of
[`FINOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Finance/Governance/canonicals/FINOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
(FINANCE-AREA-FULL per **D-IH-88-E**).

## When this rule applies

- Mint or modify Finance plane-2/3 registries under `Finance/Governance/canonicals/dimensions/`.
- Mint or modify `FINOPS_COUNTERPARTY_REGISTER.csv` or sibling finops CSVs.
- Touch `DATA_CONTRACT_REGISTRY` DC-HOL-FINOPS-* rows.
- Run monthly recon or interpret `finops.registered_fact` writer paths.
- Wire FINOPS validators into `validate_hlk.py` or `dataops_quality_check.py --data-fam FINOPS-SPINE`.

## RULE 1 — Five FINOPS dimensions before commit (binding)

Every FINOPS tranche must satisfy FIN-01..05 from
[`FINOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Finance/Governance/canonicals/FINOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
§2:

- **FIN-01** Register integrity → `validate_finops_ledger.py` + `validate_hlk.py`
- **FIN-02** Mirror parity → `dataops_quality_check.py --data-fam FINOPS-SPINE`
- **FIN-03** Join spine → Stripe link coverage (live SQL at incorporation)
- **FIN-04** Entity gate → no production monetary amounts in git until `thi_finan_dtp_306`
- **FIN-05** Cross-area contract → DC-HOL-FINOPS-* rows for bridges

## RULE 2 — Entity gate blocks production facts in git (binding)

Do not commit production invoice amounts, live Stripe charge totals, or
operator payroll figures into canonical CSVs. `finops.registered_fact` rows
live in Supabase; git holds **policy, registers, and validators** only.

## RULE 3 — Counsel-encoded tax obligations (binding)

Tax calendar rows (`FINOPS_TAX_CALENDAR.csv`) carry **cadence rules** and AEAT
references — not invented deadlines. Entity-specific `next_due_at` values are
counsel / AT-Pymes confirmed per **D-IH-81-P**.

## RULE 4 — Monthly recon cadence (binding post-F3)

Run `scripts/finops_monthly_recon.py --report` at month close; file evidence
under `docs/wip/planning/88-cross-area-ops-wiring-review-discipline/reports/finops-recon-YYYY-MM.md`.

